        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">The "original" person who came up with the idea of Bond of Death and our other spells was a combination of ideas from the first necros and the magic designer of EQ Geoffrey Zatkin(Arch-Mage of Norrath).  </P><P>And if you were wondering, GZ is now lead designer for Verant's MMORTS: Sovereign, and has probably passed the mantle of being lead designer of the EQ magic system to another person.  Whether if the "role" of us necros were lost in this exchange, decide for yourself.  All I'm going to say is that more often than not, when a game is as successful as EQ, people who inherit the game from the original designers are much more content to not "rock the boat" then to implement changes that could possibly destroy the success.  It's a prudent business decision, and that's what EQ is - a business.  </P><P>The true role of the necro class is anyone's guess nowadays, and for that I am afraid.  Back then when GZ was still on the EQ team, at least you knew what to expect since his idea of the necros is probably the way the class is going to be.  Now, I don't know, it seems more like that Verant is more concerned with appeasing the players than keeping any coherent design for the classes, and that scares me.</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
